Text formatters
---------------

CSS can be reformatted.

    >>> from gdp.format import Formatter
    >>> from testing.gedithelpers import get_window

    >>> window, view, document = get_window('plugins/gdp/data/snark.css')
    >>> formatter = Formatter(window)
    >>> document.select_range(
    ...     document.get_start_iter(), document.get_end_iter())
    >>> formatter.reformat_css(None)
    >>> print formatter.text #doctest: -NORMALIZE_WHITESPACE
    .snark {
        font-style: italic;
        color: #ff0000;
        }
    .baker {
        font-style: italic;
        color: #3333ff;
        }
    .banker {
        font-style: italic;
        color: #666;
        }
    ...

CSS can be checked.

    >>> from gdp.formatcheck import CSSChecker

    >>> CSSChecker('snark.css', formatter.text).check()
    14: Unknown Property name.: font-crack
    15: Invalid value for "CSS Color Module Level 3/CSS Level 2.1"
        property: none: color
